We, the undersigned, welcome the Prime Minister's recent comments in the wake of the recent riots, regarding zero tolerance against dishonesty.

We therefore urge him to lead by example, to set a standard for the rest of the country by taking a stand of zero tolerance against the documented and admitted dishonesty with regard to expenses of the following ministers still currently serving in his government:
Michael Gove, Secretary of State for Education;
Alan Duncan, MInister for International Development;
Andrew Lansley, Secretary of State for Health;
Oliver Letwin, Minister of State at the Cabinet Office;
George Osborne, Chancellor of the Exchequer;
David Willetts, Minister for Universities and Science.

We urge the Prime Minister to abandon the inflammatory hypocrisy of taking one attitude towards a looter of £3.50 worth of bottled water and another towards the fraudulent claimant of £7000 in expenses.
